NodeJS:
    - NodeJS is the server side scripting language.
    - by using NodeJS, we can create the http&tcp servers.
    - in general node applications we can develop by using javascript.

modules in NodeJS:
-----------------
1. express
    - this module used to develop the Rest API.

2. mysql
    - this module used to interact with the mysql database.

3.mongodb
    - this module used to interact with the mongodb.

4. http
    - this module used to create the http servers.

5.body-parser
    - this module used to set the MIME Type.
    Ex.
        text
        json
        xml
        --
        --
        --
6.jwt-simple
    - this module used to  maintain the token based authentication system.

7.fs
    - this module used to interact with the flat files.
    Ex.
        text files
        json files
        xml files
            --
            --
            --
8.multer
    - this module used to handle the multimedia images.

9.cluster
     - this module used to implement the clustering in node applications.

- in general we will download the node modules by using "package.json" file.

- we can execute the package.json file by using "npm install" command.


Ex_1:
    Basic Communication Between Angular and Node.

------------------------
Node_BasicEx

        index.html

        package.json

        server.js
-----------------------

package.json
{
    "name":"nareshit",
    "version":"1.0.0",
    "description":"basic node example",
    "dependencies":{
        "express":"latest"
    }
}


>npm install


server.js
---------
//import express
var express = require("express");


//create the server instance
var app = express();


//deploy the application
app.use(express.static(__dirname+"/../Node_BasicEx"));


//assign the port no.
app.listen(8080);
console.log("Server Listening the Port No.8080");


>npm start
[Startup the Server]



